{"lemma":"أَيْمانُ","slug":"أَيْمانُ","root":"#.م.ن","root_slug":"_-م-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/_-م-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"يَمِين","root":"يمن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":65},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1274","n1623"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"right, right side (opposed to left)","examples":[{"text":"ثُمَّ ٱنْعَطِفْ يَمِينًا.","english":"Then, turn right."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"right hand","examples":[{"text":"وَمَا تِلْكَ بِيَمِينِكَ يَا مُوسَى","english":"And what is that in your right hand, O Moses?"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"oath"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Power"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"oath"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *yamīn- (“right”), from Proto-Afroasiatic *yamin- (“right”)."},"ipa":["/ja.miːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1274","headword_ar":"اـِيمَانٌ","root":"Amn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of 4, q. v. ―         -b2-  Used as a simple subst.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Belief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in God, and in his word and apostles &c.: faith: trust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confidence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] ―         -b3-  Sometimes it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prayer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaApN","text_ar":"صَلَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": as in the Kur [ii. 138], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA kaAna All~`hu liyuDiyEa A_iyamAnakumo","text_ar":"وَمَا كَانَ اللّٰهُ لِيُضِيعَ اـِيَمانَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd, Jel, TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God will not make to be lost"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"your prayer"},{"kind":"page_break","n":103},{"kind":"text","text":"towards Jerusalem, (Bd, * Jel,) as some explain it. (Bd.) ―         -b4-  Sometimes, also, it is used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The law brought by the Prophet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Bd","Jel","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n1623","headword_ar":"اَيْمَانُ","root":"Aym","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose wife has died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomaY","text_ar":"اَيْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose husband has died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayaAmaY","text_ar":"اَيَامَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", of both; like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakaAray","text_ar":"سَكَارَي"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoraAnu","text_ar":"سَكْرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to ISk,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayaAmaY","text_ar":"اَيَامَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayaAy^imu","text_ar":"اَيَايِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~imN","text_ar":"اَيِّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomaAnu EayomaAnu","text_ar":"اَيْمَانُ عَيْمَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are epithets applied to a man, (M, K, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whose wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have died"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perished"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he has no wife and is vehemently desirous of milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as shown above; see 1, last signification]: (TA:) the former relates to wives; and the latter, to milk: (S, K, TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayomaY EayomaY","text_ar":"اَيْمَى عَيْمَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman. (M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA","S"]}]}}